[{"question":"What do you think needs to be done?","answer":"Well, it was a horrific day.","docId":"130320pmt","qSentId":51,"aSentId":52},{"question":"Do you think that if America had seen what you saw there would be any doubt about banning assault weapons?","answer":"I think it may help.","docId":"130320pmt","qSentId":65,"aSentId":66},{"question":"Why is it so important that there should be one?","answer":"You know, I heard the president say they deserve a vote.","docId":"130320pmt","qSentId":93,"aSentId":94},{"question":"What do you say to that?","answer":"I respect the Second Amendment.","docId":"130320pmt","qSentId":114,"aSentId":115},{"question":"Actually I think you\u0027ve got two Purple Hearts, am I right?","answer":"Yes, sir.","docId":"130320pmt","qSentId":124,"aSentId":125},{"question":"Of the three planks, really, of what Dianne Feinstein, the senator, is trying to push through, assault weapons, background checks, and the magazine, which of those things that do you feel strongest about?","answer":"Background checks.","docId":"130320pmt","qSentId":140,"aSentId":141},{"question":"Why?","answer":"I think the background checks are very important.","docId":"130320pmt","qSentId":142,"aSentId":143},{"question":"Who takes possession of those weapons for the short term until it\u0027s decided who they should go to?","answer":"Right.","docId":"130320pmt","qSentId":171,"aSentId":172},{"question":"And that\u0027s the point of this, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"Well, certainly, on the surface, it is.","docId":"130320pmt","qSentId":205,"aSentId":206},{"question":"Sheriff, are you -- are you saying you\u0027re not going to even try and enforce the law?","answer":"Mr. Morgan, again, I don\u0027t think that there\u0027s any ability for -- I or my officers or other officers armed around the state to determine if a magazine that comes into our inspection was acquired before or after the ban.","docId":"130320pmt","qSentId":227,"aSentId":228},{"question":"At Sandy Hook, had he had 100 bullet magazine, he could have killed a lot more in the same period of time, right?","answer":"And you\u0027re right.","docId":"130320pmt","qSentId":252,"aSentId":253},{"question":"And I would also like you to answer the point, if it saves one life of one child in a future mass shooting in your state, even in the area that you\u0027re the sheriff, isn\u0027t it worth it?","answer":"If I thought that was the fact, yes, sir.","docId":"130320pmt","qSentId":267,"aSentId":268},{"question":"Who is going to miss 30, 40, 50 bullet magazines?","answer":"I think there\u0027s a -- I think there\u0027s a major concern which I concur with.","docId":"130320pmt","qSentId":289,"aSentId":290},{"question":"What do you say to that?","answer":"I say that it\u0027s our responsibility to enforce the law, whatever it is.","docId":"130320pmt","qSentId":295,"aSentId":296},{"question":"But underneath all that, what is the reality of the state of the relationship between America and Israel right now?","answer":"There\u0027s no question, Piers, it\u0027s been obvious to the world, not just to these two leaders, that they\u0027ve had a very frosty and somewhat unfriendly relationship.","docId":"130320pmt","qSentId":328,"aSentId":329},{"question":"What do we really know about what may have happened here?","answer":"Not much, which is part of the issue.","docId":"130320pmt","qSentId":346,"aSentId":347},{"question":"Now there is so much tension all over the region, it\u0027s no longer just about Israel and Palestine, is it?","answer":"No, it isn\u0027t.","docId":"130320pmt","qSentId":369,"aSentId":370},{"question":"And is that going to be discussed over the next couple of days?","answer":"Well, it will be discussed in the morning.","docId":"130320pmt","qSentId":379,"aSentId":380},{"question":"How crucial is this going to be, this part of the debate?","answer":"Yeah.","docId":"130320pmt","qSentId":395,"aSentId":396},{"question":"I mean, do you not think they should, at the very least, be pushing forward to a vote, so that everyone can see who is in favor and who is against?","answer":"I don\u0027t know all of the issues, because I don\u0027t follow them in nearly as much detail as when I myself was there.","docId":"130320pmt","qSentId":412,"aSentId":413},{"question":"Are you remotely optimistic?","answer":"I am very optimistic.","docId":"130320pmt","qSentId":466,"aSentId":467},{"question":"Do you agree with that?","answer":"No, I don\u0027t.","docId":"130320pmt","qSentId":494,"aSentId":495},{"question":"Are you optimistic that within five years there could be a peace deal?","answer":"Well, we did a poll on that.","docId":"130320pmt","qSentId":514,"aSentId":515},{"question":"Alan?","answer":"Well, if the Palestinians sit down and negotiate, the Israelis will make a very generous offer, as they did in 2000, 2001 and 2007.","docId":"130320pmt","qSentId":527,"aSentId":528},{"question":"How are you going to stop the migration, which has been going on now for quite some time, of your product to Apple and indeed to Samsung and Android?","answer":"The way we stop this is we have built this new product and platform, Blackberry 10, because we knew we had to come up with something really exciting and new.","docId":"130320pmt","qSentId":576,"aSentId":577},{"question":"Or were you hoping they\u0027re outdated?","answer":"No, I think with Z-10 coming to market, I think they are falling behind in terms of the user interface.","docId":"130320pmt","qSentId":603,"aSentId":604},{"question":"What is the single best way you are going do hook them back with these new things?","answer":"The single best way is, first, the user interface we talked about.","docId":"130320pmt","qSentId":621,"aSentId":622}]